notesStmt.note: Slight damp entry at ends; some tidemarks and mould-spotting.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 29; written lines: 29; Uniform layout. Complete hard-point ruling (also for marginalia) visible. Hair side and flesh side of folios hardly distinguishable. Larger initial words. Additions and notes in the margins. Running titles. Last word of a folio repeated at the beginning of the next.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 15th to 16th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Ibn Sina. Kanun. Hebrew. Vol. III. Brit. Mus. Oriental 6891.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Purchased by the British Museum through Sassoon & Co. on 07 April 1903: inscribed, folio [187v] (fse001v).
